This paper deals with the problem of finding heavy hitters in high-dimensional data streams, which is a fundamental problem in data stream theory, databases, networking, and signal processing. The problem is applicable in a wide range of fields, including machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
